## 2) Kinematics (1D & 2D)

### Key equations for constant acceleration (1D)
- v = u + at
- s = ut + ½at²
- v² = u² + 2as
- Trick: “Very Ugly Astronauts” (v = u + at), “Some United Astronauts” (s = ut + ½at²), “Very Very Ugly Astronauts” (v² = u² + 2as).

### Projectile motion (level ground)
- Time of flight: T = 2u sinθ / g
- Max height: H = u² sin²θ / (2g)
- Range: R = u² sin2θ / g
- Max range at θ = 45° (sin2θ = 1).
- At highest point: vertical velocity = 0; acceleration = g (downward); horizontal velocity constant = u cosθ.

### Relative velocity
- vAB = vA – vB (vector subtraction). If they’re in opposite directions, add speeds.

