## 3) Laws of Motion & Friction

### Newton’s laws (memory: “1–2–3 rule”)
- 1st: Law of inertia; no net force ⇒ constant velocity (a = 0).
- 2nd: Fnet = ma.
- 3rd: Every action has equal & opposite reaction; forces act on different bodies.

### Friction
- Static friction (fs) ≤ μs N; kinetic friction fk = μk N.
- μs > μk generally.
- Angle of friction: tan λ = μ.
- Angle of repose: tan θ = μ (block just starts to slide).

### Tension & pulleys
- Light & smooth pulley: tension same on both sides.
- Acceleration of system: a = (m₂ – m₁)g / (m₁ + m₂) (Atwood machine).

