## 5) Rotational Motion

### Moment of inertia (I)
- I = Σmr².
- Standard I (learn these; many questions pick from here):
  - Ring about centre: MR²
  - Ring about diameter: ½MR²
  - Disc about centre: ½MR²
  - Solid sphere: ⅖MR²
  - Hollow spherical shell: ⅔MR²
  - Rod about centre: 1/12 ML²
  - Rod about end: ⅓ML²

### Parallel & perpendicular axes
- Parallel axis: I = Icm + Md².
- Perpendicular axis (lamina only): Iz = Ix + Iy.

### Rolling without slipping
- v = ωR.
- a = αR.
- Total KE = translational + rotational = ½mv² + ½Iω².

### Angular momentum & torque
- L = Iω; τ = dL/dt.
- τ = rF sinθ (direction via right‑hand rule).
- Conservation of L: τnet = 0 ⇒ L constant.

