## 6) Gravitation

### Newton’s law
- F = Gm₁m₂ / r².
- Gravitational potential: V = –GM/r (negative).
- Potential energy: U = –GMm/r.

### Orbital speed & escape
- Orbital speed near planet surface: v = √(GM/R) ≈ √(gR).
- Escape velocity: ve = √(2GM/R) = √2 × orbital speed.
- Trick: “Escape = root two × orbital.”

### Kepler’s laws
- 1st: Orbits are elliptical; Sun at one focus.
- 2nd: Equal areas in equal times (r²ω = constant ⇒ sweeps equal area).
- 3rd: T² ∝ r³ (or T²/r³ = constant).

