## 7) Properties of Matter & Fluids

### Elasticity
- Young’s modulus: Y = stress/strain = (F/A) / (ΔL/L).
- Bulk modulus: B = –ΔP / (ΔV/V).
- Modulus of rigidity (shear): η = shear stress / shear strain.

### Viscosity
- Poiseuille’s formula: Q = πPr⁴ / (8ηl).
- Stoke’s law (sphere): F = 6πηrv.

### Surface tension
- Excess pressure inside:
  - Liquid drop: 2S/R.
  - Bubble in air: 4S/R.
- Capillary rise: h = 2S cosθ / (rρg).

### Bernoulli’s principle
- P + ½ρv² + ρgh = constant (along streamline).

