## 8) Thermodynamics & Kinetic Theory

### Laws of thermodynamics
- Zeroth: Temperature equality (thermal equilibrium).
- First: ΔQ = ΔU + ΔW (energy conservation).
- Second: Heat flows from hot to cold; entropy of isolated system never decreases; Kelvin‑Planck/Clausius statements.
- Third: At T = 0 K, entropy → constant (minimum).

### Processes (ideal gas)
- Isobaric: P constant; W = PΔV.
- Isochoric: V constant; W = 0.
- Isothermal: T constant; ΔU = 0; Q = W.
- Adiabatic: Q = 0; PVγ = constant; TVγ⁻¹ = constant.

### Specific heats
- Cp – Cv = R (molar).
- γ = Cp / Cv.
- For monoatomic ideal gas: Cv = 3R/2; Cp = 5R/2; γ = 5/3 ≈ 1.67.

### Kinetic theory of gases
- Average KE: 3/2 kT per molecule.
- RMS speed: vrms = √(3RT/M).
- Pressure: P = ⅓ (mn/V) vrms² = ⅓ρvrms².

