## 9) Oscillations & Waves

### SHM basics
- a = –ω²x; F = –kx.
- x(t) = A cos(ωt + φ); v = –Aω sin(ωt + φ); a = –Aω² cos(ωt + φ).
- T = 2π/ω; f = 1/T.
- Energy (total) = ½kA² (constant).

### Simple pendulum
- T = 2π √(L/g).
- For small θ; independent of mass.

### Spring–mass system
- T = 2π √(m/k).
- Parallel springs: keq = k₁ + k₂.
- Series springs: 1/keq = 1/k₁ + 1/k₂.

### Wave (progressing)
- v = fλ.
- y = A sin(kx – ωt); k = 2π/λ; ω = 2πf.

### Sound
- In gases: v = √(γP/ρ) = √(γRT/M).
- Doppler: f′ = f (v ± vo) / (v ∓ vs); signs depend on direction (towards vs away).

### Beats
- Beat frequency = |f₁ – f₂|.
- When two close frequencies sound together, periodic loud/soft.

### Standing waves (strings & pipes)
- String fixed both ends: L = n(λ/2); harmonics: f, 2f, 3f, ...
- Open pipe: L = n(λ/2); all harmonics.
- Closed pipe: L = (2n–1)λ/4; odd harmonics only.

