## 10) Electrostatics

### Coulomb’s law
- F = k q₁q₂ / r²; k = 1/(4πε₀).

### Electric field & potential
- E = F/q; V = W/q.
- For point charge: V = kQ/r; E = kQ/r².
- Relation: E = –dV/dx.

### Dipole
- Dipole moment: p = q × 2a (vector from –q to +q).
- On axial line: E = 2kp/r³.
- On equatorial line: E = kp/r³.
- Torque in uniform E: τ = p × E; PE = –p·E = –pE cosθ.

### Gauss’s law
- Φ = ∮E·dA = Qenclosed/ε₀.
- Useful for: infinite line, infinite plane, thin shell, solid sphere (field inside/outside).

### Capacitance
- Single plate: C = Q/V; parallel plate: C = ε₀A/d.
- Dielectric: C′ = κC₀.
- Energy: U = ½CV² = ½QV = Q²/(2C).
- Series: 1/Ceq = 1/C₁ + 1/C₂; parallel: Ceq = C₁ + C₂.

