## 11) Current Electricity

### Ohm’s law
- V = IR; R = ρL/A.

### Kirchhoff’s laws
- Junction: ΣI = 0.
- Loop: ΣV = 0 (including EMFs and IR drops).

### Cells & combinations
- Emf (E); internal resistance (r).
- Terminal voltage: V = E – Ir (discharging).
- Series: Eeq = E₁ + E₂; req = r₁ + r₂.
- Parallel: for identical cells E₁ = E₂ = E: Eeq = E; req = r/n.

### Wheatstone bridge
- Balance condition: P/Q = R/S ⇒ no current through galvanometer.

### Meter bridge & potentiometer
- Meter bridge: balanced when R/S = l₁/l₂.
- Potentiometer measures emf/unknown potential; null deflection (no current drawn at balance).

### Heating effect
- H = I²Rt; Power: P = I²R = V²/R = VI.
- Trick: In series, use P = I²R; in parallel, use P = V²/R.

