## 12) Magnetism & EMI

### Biot–Savart & Ampere
- Straight wire: B = μ₀I / (2πr).
- At centre of circular loop: B = μ₀I / (2R).
- Solenoid: B = μ₀nI (inside); n = turns per unit length.

### Force on charge/current in magnetic field
- Lorentz force: F = q(v × B).
- Current element: dF = I dl × B.
- Moving charge in uniform B → circular motion: r = mv/(qB); T = 2πm/(qB).

### Magnetic moment
- Current loop: M = IA.
- Torque: τ = M × B.

### EM induction (Faraday & Lenz)
- Faraday: emf ε = –dΦ/dt.
- Lenz: direction of induced emf opposes change in flux.
- Motional emf: ε = Blv (conductor perpendicular to B and v).

### Self & mutual inductance
- Self: ε = –L dI/dt; energy: U = ½LI².
- Mutual: ε₂ = –M dI₁/dt.

### AC basics
- V = V₀ sin(ωt); I = I₀ sin(ωt ± φ).
- Impedance (Z): for R only Z = R; for L: ZL = ωL; for C: ZC = 1/(ωC).
- Series LCR: Z = √[R² + (XL – XC)²].
- Resonance: XL = XC; Z = R (minimum); current maximum; f₀ = 1/(2π√LC).
- Power: P = Vrms Irms cosφ; cosφ = power factor.

### Transformer
- Turns ratio: Vs/Vp = Ns/Np = Ip/Is.
- Step‑up: Ns > Np; step‑down: Ns < Np.
- Works only on AC.

