## 13) Optics (Ray & Wave)

### Reflection & mirrors
- Mirror formula: 1/f = 1/v + 1/u.
- Magnification: m = –v/u = hᵢ/hₒ.
- Sign (Cartesian): u –ve (object left); f –ve (concave: f < 0, convex: f > 0 in same sign rules).

### Refraction & lenses
- Snell’s law: n₁ sin i = n₂ sin r.
- Lens formula: 1/f = 1/v – 1/u (according to NCERT sign convention; in real‑is‑positive convention adjust).
- Lens maker’s formula: 1/f = (n–1)(1/R₁ – 1/R₂).
- Power: P = 1/f (in metres); unit D (dioptre).
- Combined lenses: P = P₁ + P₂ (thin lenses in contact).

### Total internal reflection & optical fibre
- Condition: i > ic; n₁ > n₂.
- Critical angle: sin ic = n₂/n₁.
- Optical fibre: TIR + cladding of lower n.

### Prism
- Deviation δ = i₁ + i₂ – A.
- Minimum deviation: δm; n = sin[(A+δm)/2] / sin(A/2).

### Wave optics
- Interference (Young’s double slit):
  - Fringe width: β = λD/d.
  - Maxima: path diff = nλ; minima = (2n–1)λ/2.
- Diffraction: single slit central maxima widest; width ∝ λ/a.
- Polarization: light with E confined to one plane; Malus’ law I = I₀ cos²θ.

