## 14) Modern Physics (Atoms, Nuclei, Dual Nature)

### Bohr model (H‑like)
- Radius: rₙ ∝ n²/Z; Energy: Eₙ ∝ –Z²/n².
- Rydberg: 1/λ = RZ²(1/n₁² – 1/n₂²).
- Transition: energy emitted = hf = hc/λ.

### Photoelectric effect
- Einstein: hf = φ₀ + KEmax; φ₀ = work function.
- Threshold frequency: f₀ = φ₀/h; below this no emission.
- Stopping potential: eVs₀ = KEmax.

### de Broglie wavelength
- λ = h/p = h/(mv); for charged particles: λ = h/√(2mqV).

### Radioactivity
- Decay law: N = N₀ e^(–λt); A = λN.
- Half‑life: T½ = ln2/λ ≈ 0.693/λ.
- Mean life: τ = 1/λ = T½/0.693.
- α: He nucleus (2p, 2n); β⁻: electron; β⁺: positron; γ: high‑energy photon.

### Mass–energy & binding energy
- E = mc².
- Mass defect: Δm = (Zmp + Nmn) – M; binding energy = Δm c².
- Binding energy per nucleon max near Fe (~56) – most stable.

### X‑rays
- Produced when fast electrons hit target.
- Continuous spectrum (bremsstrahlung) + characteristic lines (Kα, Kβ).
- Moseley’s law: √f ∝ Z.

