## 15) Semiconductors & Electronics

### Band theory
- Conductors: overlapping valence/conduction bands.
- Insulators: large gap.
- Semiconductors: small gap; Si, Ge.

### Intrinsic & extrinsic
- Intrinsic: pure Si/Ge; ne = nh.
- n‑type: pentavalent dopant (P, As); electrons as majority carriers.
- p‑type: trivalent dopant (B, Al); holes as majority.

### p‑n junction diode
- Forward bias: conduction; low resistance.
- Reverse bias: small leakage (saturation current).
- Breakdown: Zener/avalanche.

### Rectifiers
- Half‑wave: 1 diode; efficiency ~40.6%.
- Full‑wave centre‑tap: 2 diodes; efficiency ~81.2%.
- Full‑wave bridge: 4 diodes; no centre tap needed; efficiency ~81.2%.

### Logic gates
- AND: output high when all inputs high.
- OR: output high when any input high.
- NOT: inverts input.
- NAND: AND + NOT.
- NOR: OR + NOT.
- XOR: output high when inputs differ.

