## 17) Memory Tricks & Mnemonics (Physics)

### Electromagnetic spectrum order (radio → gamma)
- “Rabbits Mate In Very Unusual X‑ray Gardens”
- Radio, Microwave, Infrared, Visible, Ultraviolet, X‑rays, Gamma rays. 【turn0search10】【turn0search11】

### SI prefixes (tera to pico)
- “The Great Mega King Killed Dwarf Man Nano Puppy Picofarad” (Giga, Mega, Kilo, Deci, Milli, Micro, Nano, Pico).
- Trick: 10¹² T, 10⁹ G, 10⁶ M, 10³ k, 10⁻² d, 10⁻³ m, 10⁻⁶ μ, 10⁻⁹ n, 10⁻¹² p.

### Thermodynamic processes
- “Pressure Is Temperature’s Almost Valuable Asset” (Isobaric, Isothermal, Isochoric, Adiabatic).

### Colour code of resistors (band colours)
- “BB ROY of Great Britain Has Very Good Wife”
- Black 0, Brown 1, Red 2, Orange 3, Yellow 4, Green 5, Blue 6, Violet 7, Grey 8, White 9, Gold 5%, Silver 10%.

### Lens sign
- “Real Is Positive” (RIP) for focal length in many Indian textbooks’ convention; but in NCERT sign conventions, check directions. Better to memorise one convention and stick to it.

### Optics: action of lenses
- Convex lens converges; concave diverges.
- Trick: Convex “Caves Inward”? No. Think “Convex = Converging”. (Similar trick for concave mirrors = converging).

### Right‑hand rule (directions)
- Fleming’s right‑hand: generator (induced current).
- Fleming’s left‑hand: motor (force).
- Right‑hand grip: current → magnetic field around wire.

