## 19) Exam‑Day Tricks for Physics

- Formula recall: When you see a keyword (projectile → immediately write T, H, R formulas; capacitor → write C, U, series/parallel).
- Units check: If answer has mismatched SI units, it’s wrong.
- Dimension check: When stuck, plug in M, L, T dimensions to test options.
- Graph sketching: Recognize slopes (dy/dx) and areas (∫y dx) – NEET loves “what does slope/area represent?”.
